WEBVTT

00:05.139 --> 00:07.969
You know, I can now bite
my fingernails so evenly...

00:08.042 --> 00:10.201
I don't even need
to use a clipper anymore.

00:10.278 --> 00:11.970
But it's a pleasure to use clippers.

00:12.046 --> 00:15.411
Why gnaw away like a mental patient
when we have this elegant device?

00:18.953 --> 00:20.418
What if you're in prison?

00:20.488 --> 00:23.318
- You don't think they give clippers?
- No, it's like a weapon.

00:23.391 --> 00:25.789
You know what's really a weapon,
that big toenail.

00:25.860 --> 00:29.623
You let that grow for a month,
take it in the shower, it's like a shiv.

00:31.299 --> 00:32.729
I love prison.

00:32.800 --> 00:34.959
It is fascinating.

00:35.203 --> 00:38.500
Yeah, maybe someday.

00:44.345 --> 00:47.278
You want me to find
a poem about Susan?

00:47.348 --> 00:49.473
May she rest in peace.

00:49.951 --> 00:54.112
Well, we think it would be a nice touch
for the foundation literature.

00:54.222 --> 00:56.916
You have a favorite poet, George?

00:57.959 --> 01:01.460
I like Flavman.

01:02.663 --> 01:05.391
- Pardon?
- Flavman.

01:06.367 --> 01:09.163
Well, you should choose the poem
since you knew Susan best...

01:09.237 --> 01:13.171
at the time
of her unfortunate... accident.

01:17.378 --> 01:19.571
- He cleared his throat?
- Yes.

01:19.647 --> 01:20.975
So?

01:21.048 --> 01:24.584
He did it right as he said,
"Her unfortunate accident."

01:24.652 --> 01:25.946
Not getting it.

01:26.020 --> 01:28.884
Jerry, a throat clear is a non-verbal
implication of doubt.

01:28.956 --> 01:30.489
He thinks I killed Susan.

01:30.558 --> 01:33.388
Oh, help me, Rhonda.

01:34.996 --> 01:37.155
- What time is it?
- One-fifteen.

01:37.231 --> 01:38.821
Right now?

01:39.634 --> 01:41.497
I gotta go meet Pam.

01:41.569 --> 01:43.500
Oh, the bookstore girl.
How's that going?

01:43.571 --> 01:46.333
Okay. I'm just not gaga over her.

01:46.407 --> 01:47.997
For once, I'd like to be gaga.

01:48.075 --> 01:49.403
Where's Elaine?

01:49.477 --> 01:51.272
She's having Carol,
Gail and Lisa over.

01:51.345 --> 01:52.912
You know, they all have kids now.

01:52.980 --> 01:54.945
What's with all these people
having babies?

01:55.016 --> 01:57.516
- Perpetuation of the species.
- Yeah, right.

01:57.919 --> 02:00.579
- By the way, just for the record...
- No, I did not.

02:00.655 --> 02:02.279
All right.

02:03.257 --> 02:07.350
But because it comes out
of your baby, it smells good.

02:08.362 --> 02:11.363
Well, that's... That's sweet.

02:11.432 --> 02:14.695
Being a mother
has made me feel so beautiful.

02:15.369 --> 02:19.405
Elaine, you gotta have a baby.

02:19.473 --> 02:21.666
Oh, hey, you know...

02:21.742 --> 02:23.275
I had a piece of whitefish...

02:23.344 --> 02:26.106
over at Barney Greengrass
the other day and l...

02:26.414 --> 02:29.972
Elaine, move to Long lsland
and have a baby already.

02:30.051 --> 02:33.245
- I really like the city.
- The city's a toilet.

02:33.321 --> 02:35.548
When's the last time
you saw my little Adam?

02:35.623 --> 02:37.486
It was in the Hamptons.

02:37.558 --> 02:40.149
- Oh, I have pictures.
- No, no, that's okay. It's...

02:40.227 --> 02:43.922
Look at him, just look at him.

02:45.599 --> 02:48.668
Elaine was telling me about
this whitefish she had the other day.

02:48.736 --> 02:51.100
Do you really think I'm wrong
about this Wyck guy?

02:51.172 --> 02:52.830
If you really wanna test him out...

02:52.907 --> 02:54.907
why don't you try
the Jerry Lewis trick?

02:54.976 --> 02:57.510
- Jerry Lewis?
- I heard when Jerry left a meeting...

02:57.578 --> 03:00.476
he'd purposely leave a briefcase
with a tape recorder in it.

03:00.548 --> 03:04.106
After five minutes, he'd come back,
listen to what everyone said.

03:04.185 --> 03:05.877
- That's pretty paranoid.
- Yes, it is.

03:05.953 --> 03:08.453
- I like it.
- I thought you might.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.683
Hi, I'm Pam.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.088
You must be Kramer.

03:15.663 --> 03:18.926
Jerry has told me a lot about you.

03:20.167 --> 03:23.759
Well, I'm supposed to meet Jerry.
It's my day off.

03:24.071 --> 03:25.604
I work in a bookstore.

03:25.973 --> 03:27.938
Books.

03:29.443 --> 03:31.170
Careful.

03:33.647 --> 03:34.975
- Hi. Sorry I'm late.
- Hi.

03:35.049 --> 03:36.582
That's okay. Kramer let me in.

03:36.650 --> 03:38.615
If we rush,
we can still make the movie.

03:38.686 --> 03:41.016
It was really nice meeting you.

03:48.462 --> 03:49.790
I'm in trouble, buddy.

03:49.864 --> 03:51.295
I just met a woman.

03:51.365 --> 03:53.126
- Go on.
- Well...

03:54.235 --> 03:56.030
she's Jerry's girlfriend.

03:56.103 --> 03:58.569
Yes, forbidden love.

03:58.639 --> 04:00.536
She works in a bookshop.

04:00.608 --> 04:03.302
- Her name is Pam.
- Pam.

04:03.377 --> 04:06.810
I don't know the woman,
but she sounds quite fetching.

04:06.881 --> 04:09.347
I can't even speak in front of her.

04:09.417 --> 04:10.643
Jerry.

04:10.718 --> 04:13.787
What could she possibly see
in Jerry?

04:15.656 --> 04:17.485
She has delicate beauty.

04:17.558 --> 04:20.559
Jerry wouldn't know delicate
if it bludgeoned him over the head.

04:20.628 --> 04:23.561
And yet, he's my friend.

04:23.631 --> 04:25.824
And therein lies the tragedy.

04:25.900 --> 04:29.026
For I believe, sadly for you...

04:29.103 --> 04:32.434
that there is but one woman
meant for each of us.

04:32.506 --> 04:36.007
One perfect angel
for whom we are put on this earth.

04:36.077 --> 04:37.576
Oh, that's beautiful, Newman.

04:37.645 --> 04:39.645
One winsome tulip...

04:39.713 --> 04:44.773
we ceaselessly yearn for throughout
our dreary workaday lives...

04:44.852 --> 04:48.945
and you, my friend,
have found your angel.

04:49.023 --> 04:50.715
I can tell...

04:50.791 --> 04:54.691
for my heart has also been captured
by a breathless beauty...

04:54.762 --> 04:57.387
whom I fear I will never possess.

04:57.465 --> 04:59.465
I thought we were talking about me.

04:59.533 --> 05:01.533
Oh, right.

05:01.602 --> 05:03.897
Kramer, you have to confront Jerry.

05:03.971 --> 05:05.698
- Confront Jerry? I can't.
- You must.

05:05.773 --> 05:08.068
- I won't.
- You will.

05:08.142 --> 05:12.372
"Elaine, you gotta have a baby."

05:13.114 --> 05:14.806
Where are the poetry magazines?

05:14.882 --> 05:16.540
The New Yorker has poetry.

05:16.617 --> 05:18.947
Yes, The New Yorker.

05:19.019 --> 05:21.883
Why do you invite these women over
if they annoy you so much?

05:21.956 --> 05:23.284
Well, they're my friends...

05:23.357 --> 05:26.722
but they act as if having a baby
takes some kind of talent.

05:26.794 --> 05:28.589
Come on. You wanna have a baby.

05:28.662 --> 05:32.095
- Why? Because I can?
- It's the life force.

05:32.166 --> 05:34.063
I saw a show
on the mollusk last night.

05:34.135 --> 05:36.726
Elaine, the mollusk travels
from Alaska to Chile...

05:36.804 --> 05:38.667
just for a shot at another mollusk.

05:38.739 --> 05:40.067
You think you're any better?

05:40.141 --> 05:43.472
Yes, I think I am better
than the mollusk.

05:43.544 --> 05:46.306
Excuse me, I couldn't help
overhearing what you were saying.

05:46.380 --> 05:48.971
- Oh, I'm sorry...
- No, no, I think I agree with you.

05:49.049 --> 05:51.515
I mean, all this talk
about having babies.

05:51.585 --> 05:53.312
Yeah, like you must procreate.

05:53.387 --> 05:55.148
Besides, anyone can do it.

05:55.222 --> 05:57.449
Oh, it's been done to death.

05:59.426 --> 06:02.188
I should have a poem
very soon now.

06:02.263 --> 06:04.558
Are you okay, George?

06:04.632 --> 06:05.994
No, no.

06:06.734 --> 06:08.563
Not really.

06:09.737 --> 06:14.934
Ever since Susan passed on,
I have good days and bad.

06:15.743 --> 06:19.904
Some days I'm haunted
by one word:

06:19.980 --> 06:21.672
Why?

06:21.782 --> 06:23.782
Why Susan?

06:24.451 --> 06:28.248
Why wasn't it me
licking those invitations?

06:28.722 --> 06:30.881
Why am I still here?

06:32.760 --> 06:34.589
But I gotta run.

06:42.102 --> 06:45.330
Now, the stock options
for this year look quite...

06:53.214 --> 06:55.043
Briefcase.

06:58.719 --> 07:01.049
So, Kevin, if I don't want children...

07:01.121 --> 07:03.416
does that make me
a bad humanitarian?

07:03.490 --> 07:05.717
- Not at all.
- Because when you get to know me...

07:05.793 --> 07:08.191
you'll see that I'm
a pretty good humanitarian.

07:08.262 --> 07:11.195
You are doing a wonderful job,
by the way.

07:11.265 --> 07:14.334
- Thanks a lot.
- Right? Am I right?

07:14.568 --> 07:19.662
Kramer, Kramer, come here,
look at my new friend Kevin.

07:20.941 --> 07:22.668
Oh, you got a little...

07:23.077 --> 07:24.542
- You got...
- Oh, yeah.

07:24.612 --> 07:27.510
I just had two
double-fudge sundaes.

07:27.581 --> 07:29.342
Oh, are you all right?

07:29.416 --> 07:31.177
Yeah, I'll be okay.

07:32.286 --> 07:35.753
You know, Jerry has one of those
every time he bombs on stage.

07:35.823 --> 07:38.187
I'm sure he'll be sharing
his next one with Pam.

07:38.259 --> 07:39.758
Oh, no, that won't last.

07:39.827 --> 07:41.918
- What do you mean?
- He's not gaga.

07:49.770 --> 07:51.462
Let me tell you. That Jerry Lewis...

07:51.538 --> 07:53.367
you wonder how people
get to the top?

07:53.474 --> 07:55.872
It's ideas like this. Brilliant.

07:56.877 --> 07:58.569
Look at this.
What the hell happened?

07:58.646 --> 08:03.877
The whole side is damaged here,
and the lock is broken.

08:03.951 --> 08:06.246
- How long did you leave it there?
- Five minutes.

08:06.453 --> 08:07.781
What the hell happened here?

08:07.855 --> 08:10.446
Play the tape.
Maybe we'll get a clue.

08:11.292 --> 08:13.587
I have to rewind it first.

