08:31.412 --> 08:33.139
All right. All right.

08:33.212 --> 08:35.804
Did anyone notice
George's fingernails?

08:35.883 --> 08:40.477
Oh, my, yes, they look like
they were eaten away by weevils.

08:40.554 --> 08:43.748
It's kind of hot in here.
Open the window.

08:44.425 --> 08:46.152
Hey, what are you doing?

08:46.226 --> 08:48.726
Dear God!

08:51.932 --> 08:53.260
Is that it?

08:53.901 --> 08:56.492
- It stopped dead.
- What do you make of it?

08:57.171 --> 08:58.932
I don't know.

08:59.940 --> 09:02.270
Jerry, can we talk?

09:02.343 --> 09:03.671
Kind of busy here.

09:03.744 --> 09:07.041
- I'd like to talk to Jerry in private.
- Why can't I stay?

09:07.114 --> 09:08.841
Because it doesn't concern you.

09:08.916 --> 09:11.951
Well, if it doesn't concern me,
then I can stay.

09:21.362 --> 09:23.623
- So, what's on your mind?
- It's Pam.

09:23.697 --> 09:26.027
- Pam? What about Pam?
- I love her, Jerry.

09:26.567 --> 09:28.567
- You what?
- I love her.

09:28.635 --> 09:32.034
- Is that right?
- Oh, she's... She's real.

09:32.106 --> 09:35.664
She can bring home the bacon
and fry it in the pan.

09:36.110 --> 09:39.543
- What does that mean?
- Oh, and that voice.

09:39.613 --> 09:43.205
- What about her name?
- Pam? Oh, it's a beautiful name.

09:44.017 --> 09:45.709
Pam.

09:46.120 --> 09:47.983
Pam?

09:48.422 --> 09:50.183
Pam!

09:50.858 --> 09:53.290
- She's got really nice hair.
- Oh, it's incredible.

09:53.360 --> 09:55.451
Although, I might replace
her tortoise clip...

09:55.529 --> 09:58.325
with one of those velvet scrunchies.
I love those.

09:58.532 --> 10:00.190
You've got really specific tastes.

10:00.267 --> 10:01.766
Oh, I know what I want, Jerry.

10:02.169 --> 10:03.566
She got nice calves.

10:03.637 --> 10:07.366
Oh, she's a dreamboat,
but you don't like her.

10:07.441 --> 10:09.566
Maybe I could.
You're making some good points.

10:09.643 --> 10:11.643
- No, you can't, Jerry.
- But I might.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.302
- Oh, no, you don't.
- Why not?

10:13.380 --> 10:15.311
- The voice, the calves, the bacon.
- What?

10:15.382 --> 10:18.246
I think I can.
I even like the name Pam.

10:18.318 --> 10:19.680
Pam. Pam.

10:31.832 --> 10:33.593
So now he wants her
more than ever.

10:33.667 --> 10:35.132
Blast.

10:36.170 --> 10:37.601
What am I gonna do, huh?

10:37.671 --> 10:40.171
Don't despair, my friend.

10:42.709 --> 10:47.041
I won't allow your love
to go unrequited, not like mine.

10:47.114 --> 10:48.613
What, again with you?

10:48.682 --> 10:50.010
Sorry.

10:50.083 --> 10:53.084
But love is a spice
with many tastes...

10:53.153 --> 10:58.122
a dizzying array of textures
and moments.

10:59.059 --> 11:01.389
If only I could say things like that
around her.

11:01.462 --> 11:03.723
Yes.

11:04.965 --> 11:07.056
Well, I hear three distinct sounds:

11:07.134 --> 11:09.065
A low rumple...

11:09.136 --> 11:11.830
followed by a metallic squink...

11:11.905 --> 11:13.836
Yes, yes, I heard the squink.

11:13.907 --> 11:17.909
Followed by a mysterious galonk.

11:18.378 --> 11:20.742
It's a real baffler, isn't it?

11:20.814 --> 11:23.439
Well, one question
does come to mind.

11:24.985 --> 11:30.682
Have you considered just asking them
what happened to the briefcase?

11:31.492 --> 11:32.820
They would never tell me.

11:33.293 --> 11:36.226
First of all, they probably think
that I killed Susan.

11:36.296 --> 11:38.864
Besides, I don't even think
they like me.

11:38.932 --> 11:41.432
That Pam. I am gaga over her.

11:41.502 --> 11:43.001
"Gaga"? When did that happen?

11:43.070 --> 11:45.502
Yesterday, 6-ish.

11:46.740 --> 11:50.037
Well, maybe we should double.
I'm pretty gaga myself.

11:50.110 --> 11:51.837
You just met the guy yesterday.

11:51.912 --> 11:53.604
Yeah, but we have a common goal.

11:53.680 --> 11:57.011
A barren, sterile existence
that ends when you die?

11:58.218 --> 12:00.047
Yeah.

12:00.721 --> 12:02.846
You believe this guy
doesn't wanna have kids?

12:02.923 --> 12:05.685
- Yeah, of course.
- A guy will say anything to a woman.

12:05.759 --> 12:07.690
Oh, please, he wouldn't say that.

12:07.761 --> 12:11.024
Elaine, I once told a woman
that I coined the phrase:

12:11.098 --> 12:12.529
"Pardon my French."

12:14.868 --> 12:18.904
I once told a woman I don't eat cake
because it goes right to my thighs.

12:20.474 --> 12:24.032
Once told a woman
I enjoy spending time with my family.

12:27.247 --> 12:31.113
Your looks and my words
will have built the perfect beast.

12:31.184 --> 12:32.808
All right.

12:41.028 --> 12:44.564
- Oh, hi, Kramer.
- Hi, how are you?

12:44.631 --> 12:46.699
Hi, how are you?

12:47.334 --> 12:49.595
- I'm great.
- I too am well.

12:49.670 --> 12:51.499
I too am well.

12:52.739 --> 12:55.569
- Do I smell Pantene?
- Do I smell...?

12:56.310 --> 12:57.900
- Pantene!
- Pantene?

12:59.112 --> 13:00.907
Oh, my shampoo.

13:00.981 --> 13:02.673
Yeah, yeah, you know,
it is Pantene.

13:02.749 --> 13:05.283
I got a free sample of it
in with my junk mail.

13:05.352 --> 13:07.079
There really is no junk mail.

13:07.154 --> 13:09.222
Everybody wants a check
or birthday card...

13:09.289 --> 13:12.790
It requires just as much manpower
to deliver as their precious cards...

13:12.859 --> 13:15.086
Newman.

13:15.162 --> 13:16.889
What?

13:17.798 --> 13:19.126
Human. Human.

13:19.199 --> 13:23.702
It's human to be moved
by a fragrance.

13:23.770 --> 13:25.132
That's so true.

13:25.205 --> 13:28.570
Her bouquet cleaved his hardened...

13:28.642 --> 13:30.869
- Shell.
- Shell

13:30.944 --> 13:34.377
And fondled his muscled heart

13:35.215 --> 13:38.148
He imbibed her glistening spell

13:38.218 --> 13:42.311
Just before the other shoe fell

13:42.789 --> 13:44.982
Kramer, that is so lovely.

13:45.325 --> 13:49.293
It's by an unknown
20th century poet.

13:49.363 --> 13:52.489
- Oh, what's him name?
- Newman.

13:55.202 --> 13:58.100
Elaine, you changed my life.

13:58.171 --> 14:02.833
Oh, Kevin, you can go on and on
about how you don't want kids...

14:02.909 --> 14:05.375
and it sounds...
It sounds really nice...

14:05.445 --> 14:09.948
but the truth is, I don't know
if you mean it or not.

14:10.017 --> 14:12.142
I got a vasectomy this morning.

14:13.787 --> 14:16.913
Although, I have a hunch
you mean it.

14:19.192 --> 14:20.691
I just came by to tell you...

14:20.761 --> 14:25.992
I'm really, really happy
about this relationship. Really happy.

14:26.066 --> 14:30.296
Oh, well, that's nice.

14:34.341 --> 14:36.272
A velvet scrunchie.

14:38.612 --> 14:40.202
Kramer.

14:46.253 --> 14:47.786
Hello, Newman.

14:48.021 --> 14:49.645
Hello, Jerry.

14:49.723 --> 14:51.051
How's Pam?

14:51.124 --> 14:53.454
Pam? What do you care?

14:57.097 --> 14:58.789
Well, ta-ta.

14:59.833 --> 15:01.992
Wait a minute.

15:29.996 --> 15:31.723
All right, Newman, this is it.

15:31.798 --> 15:33.092
Steady, Jerry.

15:33.166 --> 15:35.860
Steady. Wouldn't wanna
lose your cool at a time like this.

15:35.936 --> 15:38.334
- Why not?
- Because right now...

15:38.405 --> 15:40.973
I'm the only chance you've got.

15:44.845 --> 15:45.934
Come on.

15:48.682 --> 15:50.807
I can't believe I'm losing Pam.

15:50.884 --> 15:52.508
I know how you feel...

15:52.586 --> 15:54.950
for I too have a woman
for whom I pine.

15:55.021 --> 15:57.954
- I thought we were talking about me.
- Right.

15:58.024 --> 16:00.092
Anyway, I don't need your help.

16:00.160 --> 16:02.125
Oh, don't you, joke boy?

16:03.764 --> 16:06.765
You really think you can manipulate
that beautiful young woman...

16:06.833 --> 16:09.424
Iike the half-soused,
nightclub rabble...

16:09.503 --> 16:13.039
that lap up your inane
"observations"?

16:14.107 --> 16:15.504
All right, Newman.

16:15.575 --> 16:18.269
What do I to get you to stop
pulling strings for Kramer?

16:18.345 --> 16:21.380
Well, there is a little something
you can do for me.

16:21.448 --> 16:22.810
Come on, out with it.

16:22.883 --> 16:25.417
It's about Elaine.

16:25.485 --> 16:27.109
Elaine? What does she have to...?

16:28.789 --> 16:31.449
Oh, no.

16:32.425 --> 16:34.857
You dated her.
Give me some inside information.

16:34.928 --> 16:36.586
Anything I can use.

16:36.863 --> 16:38.794
Well, I know she doesn't
wanna have kids.

16:42.002 --> 16:45.128
I thought you'd be
a little more enthusiastic about it.

16:45.572 --> 16:49.938
I know. I don't want... kids.

16:50.010 --> 16:52.305
- What was that?
- Well...

16:52.379 --> 16:54.174
Kevin, maybe I have a little doubt.

16:54.247 --> 16:56.315
I mean, nothing is 100 percent.

16:56.383 --> 16:58.348
This is.

16:58.885 --> 17:02.182
- Oh, boy, I always do this.
- What?

17:02.255 --> 17:05.722
I get all jazzed up about something,
and I go way too far with it.

17:05.791 --> 17:07.189
- Really?
- Oh, yeah.

17:07.260 --> 17:10.796
Like last summer, I'm watching TV
and I saw one of those jet skis.

17:11.832 --> 17:14.594
Four thousand dollars later,
and it's sitting in my garage.

17:14.667 --> 17:17.999
You know, that's weird actually,
because I'm sort of the same way.

17:18.070 --> 17:21.766
I mean, once for, like, no reason,
I flattened my hair...

17:21.842 --> 17:25.673
and I had all these strands
hanging in my face all the time.

17:25.744 --> 17:29.941
Sometimes I think I do want kids,
maybe a lot of kids.

17:30.016 --> 17:33.017
Sometimes I think about
wearing my hair real short.

17:33.086 --> 17:37.384
Yeah, I think I like short hair,
really short.

17:37.457 --> 17:39.184
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

17:43.263 --> 17:47.527
This is a crude mock-up
of the conference room.

17:47.601 --> 17:49.168
One-fourteenth scale.

17:49.402 --> 17:50.867
When did you build this thing?

17:50.937 --> 17:53.267
Yesterday. Took the day off.

17:53.773 --> 17:58.401
Now, from the time
that I left the room...

17:58.478 --> 18:00.705
- Wait. That's you?
- Yeah.

18:01.014 --> 18:02.843
I think the M&M should be you.

18:09.122 --> 18:11.053
All right, whatever.

18:11.658 --> 18:15.626
Now, whatever caused
the damage...

18:15.695 --> 18:20.061
it was jarring enough
to completely stop the tape.

18:20.133 --> 18:22.997
- And?
- Okay.

18:23.069 --> 18:25.364
That's what we know.

18:25.939 --> 18:28.735
- But we already knew that.
- Well, yeah.

18:28.808 --> 18:31.900
Just give me some idea
what you think it could be.

18:32.212 --> 18:34.780
- I don't know if you're ready for it.
- Please.

18:35.282 --> 18:39.546
I believe that I'm about
to become the target...

18:39.619 --> 18:42.984
of a systematic process
of intimidation and manipulation...

18:43.056 --> 18:46.353
- the likes of which...
- Hold it. You're right. I'm not ready.

18:49.329 --> 18:50.657
- Yeah?
- It's Pam.

18:50.730 --> 18:53.560
Come on up. All right, it's Pam.
You gotta get going.

18:53.633 --> 18:55.200
I'm not through here, Jerry.

18:55.268 --> 18:57.393
I'm gonna keep on investigating.

18:57.737 --> 18:59.202
This thing is like an onion.

18:59.272 --> 19:03.775
The more layers you peel,
the more it stinks.

19:08.415 --> 19:09.812
What was that?

19:09.883 --> 19:11.951
We were just playing.

19:13.520 --> 19:16.088
Listen, I had a long talk
with Kramer today.

19:17.057 --> 19:21.218
Well, the thing is l...
I think I have a little crush on him.

19:22.762 --> 19:24.090
I'm so happy.

19:24.164 --> 19:26.129
My world suddenly has meaning.

19:26.199 --> 19:28.324
This is the man
you have a crush on?

19:28.401 --> 19:30.469
Well, I have feelings for both of you.

19:30.537 --> 19:32.571
You have feelings for him?
We're soul mates.

19:32.639 --> 19:34.400
Why can't I be a soul mate?

19:34.474 --> 19:38.305
Jerry, you really think Pam would want
you to be the father of her children?

19:38.378 --> 19:39.809
Children?

19:39.879 --> 19:42.812
Who said anything about children?
I don't wanna have children.

19:46.453 --> 19:47.986
There are people in this room...

19:48.054 --> 19:53.114
who would've been very happy
to never see this briefcase again.

19:53.827 --> 19:55.360
There are people in this room...

19:55.428 --> 19:58.088
who think they can destroy
other people's property...

19:58.164 --> 19:59.993
and get away with it.

20:00.433 --> 20:02.797
Well, let me tell you something
about those people.

20:02.869 --> 20:05.494
They weren't
counting on this brain...

20:06.272 --> 20:08.340
and this tape recorder.

20:08.408 --> 20:10.032
- George...
- You'll have your turn.

20:12.779 --> 20:15.973
The truth must be heard.

20:16.049 --> 20:17.548
Hey, what are you doing?

20:17.851 --> 20:19.509
Dear God!

20:23.156 --> 20:24.780
That's all there was...

20:24.858 --> 20:28.689
and yet it speaks volumes.

20:29.162 --> 20:31.196
A low rumple...

20:31.831 --> 20:34.195
a metallic squink...

20:34.667 --> 20:36.735
a galonk...

20:36.803 --> 20:40.395
and someone crying out,
"Dear God!"

20:42.175 --> 20:46.905
Let's start with... With you, Wyck.

20:49.149 --> 20:52.548
George, Quinn here
was moving a chair.

20:52.619 --> 20:54.584
He lost his balance and dropped it.

20:54.654 --> 20:56.483
It must have fallen
on your briefcase...

20:56.556 --> 21:00.183
which, for some reason,
contained a running tape recorder.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.429
All right then.

21:10.236 --> 21:12.634
We've gotten to the bottom of that.

21:19.512 --> 21:20.909
What are you guys doing here?

21:20.980 --> 21:22.741
We're getting vasectomies.

21:24.284 --> 21:26.875
- Why?
- I'm doing it for you.

21:27.754 --> 21:29.879
- What?
- What did you do to your hair?

21:30.356 --> 21:31.923
I cut it.

21:31.991 --> 21:33.353
It's a little short.

21:33.426 --> 21:35.016
You think?

21:36.963 --> 21:38.189
What are you doing here?

21:38.264 --> 21:40.423
Kevin's having
his vasectomy reversed.

21:40.500 --> 21:41.897
- Reversed?
- Reversed?

22:01.588 --> 22:04.851
He imbibed her glistening spell

22:05.525 --> 22:09.459
Just before the other shoe fell

22:13.233 --> 22:14.664
Is that a Keats poem?

22:14.734 --> 22:16.324
No, it's a Newman.

22:18.938 --> 22:20.596
Well, I gotta run.

22:28.481 --> 22:31.141
Does anyone think George
might have murdered Susan?

22:31.484 --> 22:34.610
Oh, yeah, I just assumed
he murdered her.

22:34.687 --> 22:37.620
- Of course he killed her.
- So it's not just me then.

22:37.924 --> 22:40.925
All right. Back to business.

